          "Grade Category for a Course",
          "Exceptional, Excellent, Distinction, Pass, Fail ",
          "1282 students",
          "2 ICT courses at Malaysia Polytechnics",
          "Academic Spreadsheets, Repository of Academic Management System",
          "[StudID, Yeear, Class, Session, Credit Hour, Course Code, Total Marks, Grade Pointer Average]",
          "End of Course",
          "Data was collected from 2 sources to explore imbalanced multiclass classification. Authors explore the use of SMOTE to oversample the minority classes.\n\nAuthors use a combination of Filter & Wrapper Feature Selection Methods. ",
          "J48, kNN, SVM, Logistic Regression, NB, Randoim Forest",
          "10-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "{Accuracy: 0.995 - RF - SMOTE, Precision: 0.995 - RF - SMOTE, Recall: 0.995 - RF - SMOTE, F1-Score: 0.995 - RF - SMOTE}",
          "The authors attempt a ML pipeline to address the problem of data imbalance in multiclass classification.\n\nWhile interesting, the approach suffers from some implementation flaws that lead to the extremely optimistic model predictions.\n\nUsing SMOTE leads to better predictions. However, the same cannot be said of the FS techniques. While it seems benefical, most of the FS techniques used do not significantly outperform the remaining approaches.",
          "Methodologically flawed - Leakage in implementation.\n\nRequires validation on additional datasets.\n\nOnly explores SMOTE"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
